  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (ML surrogate)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a deep neural network surrogate model used in hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the ML surrogate model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A single-training-run feedforward neural network replaces the full CFD solver for rapid sensitivity sweeps across 5 flow-speed combinations. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
