    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The neural network surrogate achieves R² of 0.973 and RMSE of 0.0047 on the held-out test set, correctly identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions in 94.2% of cases. Experimental comparisons with FDA benchmark data confirm predictions within ±8%. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. The surrogate is accepted for use in COU1 to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
